Weema by Henrique Gog√≥ <henriquegogo@gmail.com>, 2022.

Window manager for minimalists

Installation:

  $ make
  $ sudo make install

Uninstall:
  
  $ sudo make uninstall

Install third party dependencies (optional):

  $ make dependencies

Usage:

  Edit .xinitrc file to 'exec weema' or select 'Weema'
  in your display manager.

Built-in binds:

  Alt+Button1: move window
  Alt+Button3: resize window
  Alt+Tab: alternate windows
  Alt+Shift+Tab: circle windows
  Alt+F4: close window
  Ctrl+Shift+W: close window
  Ctrl+Alt+Delete: exit
  Super+Shift+Arrows: resize window
  Super+Alt+Arrows: move window
  Super+Arrows: position window

Configurable binds:

  Volume up: increase volume
  Volume down: decrease volume
  PrntScr: print screen
  Super+R: open application launcher
  Super+T: open terminal
  Super+B: open browser
  Super+L: lock screen

Third party optional dependencies:
  
  We use third party applications to manage some functions.
  You can configure this editing the config.h file.

  - dmenu: applications launcher
  - slock: screen locker
  - alsa-utils: volume control
  - scrot: print screen

Tips:

  File ~/.weemarc will be executed every time the WM starts.
  Some key binds are customizable editing the config.h file.
  Custom one-letter shortcuts will be binded 'Super-Letter'.
  This window manager partialy ICCM/EWMH compliant.

